The Russian Armed Forces, including volunteer units and Cossack detachments, continue to conduct a Special Military Operation. The main thing from today’s (04/12/2024) briefing of the Ministry of Defense:— Over the week, the Russian Armed Forces in the Avdeevka direction continued to advance into the depths of the Ukrainian Armed Forces’ defense, repelling 65 counterattacks;

— The Ukrainian Armed Forces lost more than 840 military personnel and 5 US-made M777 howitzers in a week in the South Donetsk direction;

— Russian aviation and air defense shot down a Neptune missile, 12 Hammer and JDAM guided bombs, 25 MLRS shells and 1,712 drones in a week;

— The Russian Armed Forces destroyed five SAMP/T air defense missile launchers of the Ukrainian Armed Forces in a week;

— Over the course of a week, the Russian Armed Forces in the Kupyansk direction improved the situation along the front line, repulsed four counterattacks of the Armed Forces of Ukraine;

— The Ukrainian Armed Forces lost over 335 military personnel and 6 US-made M777 howitzers in a week in the Kherson direction;

— The losses of the Ukrainian Armed Forces in the Avdeevka direction in a week amounted to more than 2,130 military personnel and 6 tanks;

— The Armed Forces of Ukraine lost more than 380 military personnel and 66 pieces of equipment in the Kupyansk direction in a week;

— The Vostok group has improved the position along the front line in a week in the southern Donetsk direction;

— Russian troops defeated seven Ukrainian brigades in the Kherson direction in a week;

— Within a week, the Russian military occupied more advantageous positions in the Donetsk direction and repelled 23 counterattacks of the Ukrainian Armed Forces. The enemy lost more than 3,000 troops and three tanks. Be with us - First Cossack

